                "elements": [
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "ok so I can't get a realtime feed without credentials. "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "UBN9AFS0N"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "user",
                                "user_id": "UC2A2ARPT"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " do you have a preference? I think live replicating to ATProto is useful even if we do not want to pursue Colibri just because it unblocks things that need fresh data.\nIf we are not sure it is useful then I could backfill from Mariano's weekly dump. I could reuse Mariano's slack app and creds quickly though. Writing a distinct Slack App is a possibility but it would also need an admin to connect it to all the channels.\n\nGiven all the data is already replicated and sort of public I think reusing the existing slack app + creds is the simplest thing to do because essentially there is not much of a security risk given we are replicating anyway. Would require the least admin help."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    },
